{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "51", "S": "01"}}, "news": [{"title": "Hubballi-Dharwad civic body extends 5% property tax rebate till May-end", "para": "The Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation has extended its 5% property tax rebate until the end of May due to lower-than-expected collections. The drive began late, prompting the extension to boost the Rs 235 crore target for 2026-27, with Rs 90 crore collected so far. GIS work will also be offered free in July and August.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/hubballi-dharwad-municipal-corporation-extends-5-property-tax-rebate-until-may-31/130991917?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-65756/130991917.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Maharashtra govt to move SC against Bombay HC order on 254 acre Mira-Bhayander land: Revenue minister", "para": "Maharashtra is preparing to take its fight to the Supreme Court after a Bombay High Court ruling favored two builders' claims to 254.88 acres in Mira-Bhayander. With the land's worth in crores, the government maintains it holds rightful ownership. Revenue Minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule declared that they will vigorously defend their position, aiming to keep this critical asset in government hands.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/maharashtra-govt-to-move-sc-against-bombay-hc-order-on-254-acre-mira-bhayander-land-revenue-minister/130991327?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-74986/130991327.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Luxury tax on large houses in Kerala garners \u20b9157 crore in five years", "para": "Luxury tax on residential buildings generated Rs 157.62 crore for the state exchequer over five years, with FY2025-26 alone contributing Rs 67.66 crore. Increased revenue is attributed to a growing number of large houses and intensified tax identification efforts. The tax applies to houses exceeding a prescribed area limit, with exemptions for smaller homes and rebates for advance payments.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/luxury-tax-on-large-houses-in-kerala-garners-157-crore-in-five-years/130991598?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-680157/130991598.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}